found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["adj","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":5},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n1699","n3598"]}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"definite, definitive","tags":["definite","definitive"]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"categorical","examples":[{"text":"مَنْع بَاتّ","english":"categorical interdiction"}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to spend the night, to stay overnight","examples":[{"text":"\" إِنْ كَانَ عِنْدَكَ مَاءٌ بَاتَ فِي شَنٍّ فَٱسْقِنَا وَإِلَّا كَرَعْنَا \" . قَالَ عِنْدِي مَاءٌ بَاتَ فِي شَنٍّ . فَٱنْطَلَقَ وَٱنْطَلَقْنَا مَعَهُ إِلَى ٱلْعَرِيشِ فَحَلَبَ لَهُ شَاةً عَلَى مَاءٍ بَاتَ فِي شَنٍّ فَشَرِبَ ثُمَّ فَعَلَ مِثْلَ ذَٰلِكَ بِصَاحِبِهِ ٱلَّذِي مَعَهُ .","english":"‘If you have any water that has been kept overnight in a water skin, then give us some to drink, otherwise we will drink by putting out mouths in the basin.’ He said: ‘I have water that has been kept in a water skin. So he went and we went with him, to the shelter, where he milked a sheep for him and (mixed it with) the water that had been kept overnight in a water skin. He drank from it, then he did likewise for his Companion who was with him.”"}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to become, to have gotten into","tags":["copulative"],"examples":[{"text":"رَمَضَانُ بَاتَ عَلَى الْأَبْوَابِ وَيَفْصِلُنَا عَنْهُ أَيّامٌ مَعْدُودَةٌ","english":"Ramadan is about to happen and what separates us from it are a few days."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to continue doing, keep doing, stick to"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Derived from the active participle of بَتَّ (batta, “to fix, to determine, to decide”)."},"ipa":null}